===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|tuft}}, {{m|enm|toft}}, {{m|enm|tofte}}, an alteration of earlier {{m|enm|*tuffe}} (> Modern English {{l|en|tuff}}), from {{der|en|fro|touffe}}, {{m|fro|tuffe}}, {{m|fro|toffe}}, {{m|fro|tofe||tuft}} (modern French {{m|fr|touffe}}), from {{der|en|LL.|tufa||helmet crest}} (near Vegezio), from Germanic (compare {{cog|ang|þūf||tuft}}, {{cog|non|þúfa||mound}}, {{cog|sv|tuva||tussock; grassy hillock}}), from {{der|en|gem-pro|*þūbǭ||tube}}, {{m|gem-pro|*þūbaz}}; akin to {{cog|la|tūber||hump, swelling}}, {{cog|grc|τῡ́φη||cattail (used to stuff beds)}}. Equivalent to {{m|en|tuff}}.

